translator.solver
Interface TargetSolver

All Known Implementing Classes:
DummySolver, GeneralTargetSolver, Minion
public interface TargetSolver

Represents the solver profile of the target solver. Every target solver has to implement this interface. All the methods that are declared here are defined in the abstract class GeneralTargetSolver.java. So if you want to add another solver, just extend the abstract class GeneralTargetSolver.java. (and you get the whole functionality with just setting the features of your solver)

Author:
andrea

setFeature

void setFeature(char feature,
                boolean turnOn)
Set the feature of a solver to true or false (i.e. turn it on(true) or off (false)). Features can only be turned on if they are supported. It is also not possible to add NEW features with this method - Only features intitiated in the constructor and that are supported, can be modified.
